<div class="dialogcontainer">
	<h2>Edit Mode</h2>
	<p> Use <img id='edit_mode' style='margin-bottom: -5px' src='/XGDB/help/images/edit_mode.gif' alt='Edit Configuration' />  to change a parameter, add metadata, or configure the genome for a data update.<b>To access:</b> Click 'Configure' or 'View/Edit Configured' on the left menu, and 'Edit Configuration'.</p>
	<ul class="bullet1 indent2">
		<li>Under <span class="largerfont bold">Database Creation</span> you can modify General display information, e.g. Database Name</li>
		<li>Under <span class="largerfont bold">Spliced-Alignment Parameters</span> you can specify parameters used to splice-align transcripts and proteins.</li>
		<li>Under <span class="largerfont bold">CpGAT Parameters</span> you can specify gene annotation parameters for the run-time CpGAT tool</li>
		<li>Under <span class="largerfont bold">Database Update</span> (if database exists) you can specify additional data path /types required for a GDB Update.</li>
		<li>Under <span class="largerfont bold">GDB Display Defaults</span> you can specify a default region, add yrGATE contact info, etc.</li>
		<li>Under <span class="largerfont bold">Genome Information</span> you can add genome metadata or view current GDB statistics.</li>
	</ul>
			<span class="heading normalfont linkback"> <a class="smallerfont" href="/XGDB/help/create_gdb.php#edit_mode">View this in Help Context</a> (create_gdb.php/edit_mode)</span>
</div>